Thanks for downloading migasfree client.

To install it, make sure you have these programs installed:

    * Python >= 3.6
    * python3-requests
    * python3-requests-toolbelt
    * python3-distro
    * python3-crypto
    * python3-netifaces
    * python3-stdeb (to create a DEB package)
    * python3-cups
    * python3-rich
    * dmidecode
    * lshw >= 02.15

Then run these commands from the command prompt:

    $ cd bin
    $ ./create-package
    # <install package (deb or rpm)>

Check /etc/migasfree.conf configuration before run migasfree bin scripts. If this file not exists, you can copy it from /usr/share/doc/migasfree-client/migasfree.conf.

And enjoy!

If you want execute 'migasfree sync' with some user, you can add this line in sudoers config:

    ALL ALL=(root) NOPASSWD: /usr/bin/migasfree sync

If your migasfree server is configured over SSL, server certificate must be copied in client machine and destination path must be configured in /etc/migasfree.conf:SSL_Cert.
